Cook,<br><br>
I stand by everything that I have ever posted on this site or anywhere else. What I said about Winter Soldiers puts me right in the middle - where I am most comfortable. Sure we take some heat, but our mission as fence riders is to bring the extremes together. Now who the hell is going to argue that Spatz and Barela are not extremes?<br><br>
You were the one who invited Spatz to lunch. Your offer generated hope among several who post here. <br><br>
It is not hard to see that you are among the many who feel alienated by a nation which turned its back on returning vets. It don't mean nuthin. As long as you know in your heart that you accomplished much, why care about how others perceive you? I served and I will always feel that I did the right thing for ME. I can only account for me.<br><br>
How long were you a cop, doing a thankless job? My dear wife has been a nurse for almost 20 years. Another thankless job. She has seen more death and tragedy than I have. <br><br>
Serving one's country is a thankless job. But, at least you know in your heart that you did the right thing. All the rest is superflous.<br><br>
As for you and Doc spatz, I like both of you as much as cyberspace allows. I can't help it, I'll always straddle the fence. <br><br>
I encourage you to go to lunch together - only this time leave prejudgements of each other behind.<br><br>

